==Chinese==
===[[Mandarin]]===
[[Pinyin]]: héshì

===Adjective===
'''[[合]][[適]]'''

# suitable; applicable; appropriate; convenient; fit; becoming
#: ''[[隨]][[著]][[企業]][[業務]][[變]][[得]][[越來越]][[複雜]]，[[伺服器]][[選擇]]'''合適'''[[的]][[作業]][[系統]][[也]][[就]][[顯得]][[越來越]][[重要]]。''<sup>1</sup>
#: ''As business transactions become increasingly complex, choosing an '''appropriate''' operating system for your server appears to be more and more important.''
# to have a good fit; to be in place

<sup>1</sup>Note that the Chinese words for "server" and "operating system" are different from the [[Simplified Chinese]] version.  See [[wikipedia:Taiwanese Mandarin|Taiwanese Mandarin]] for an in depth explanation.

